---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Sidebar from '../layouts/Sidebar.astro'
import Socials from '../content/socials.astro'
---

<Base>
  <Sidebar style="terms">
    <main>
      <div class="content">
        <h1>Code of Conduct</h1>
        <p>Last updated: 30/03/2026</p>
        <p>
          Flüüfff is committed to creating a safe, respectful, and welcoming environment for everyone. By attending the
          convention, you agree to follow the rules below. These are here to ensure all attendees, whether it's your
          first con or your fiftieth, can enjoy the experience fully and comfortably.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>1. Respect and Inclusion</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Harassment, discrimination, or inappropriate behavior of any kind will not be tolerated.</li>
          <li>Always ask for consent — whether it's for a photo, a hug, or a conversation.</li>
          <li>
            If you experience or witness something that makes you uncomfortable, please report it to a staff member.
            We're here to help.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>2. Badges and Identification</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Convention badges must be worn visibly at all times within convention areas.</li>
          <li>
            Badges are personal and non-transferable. Sharing, duplicating, or altering badges is strictly prohibited.
          </li>
          <li>Attendees must be at least 18 years old and may be asked to show ID at check-in or during the event.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>3. Attire, Clothing, and Fursuiting</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            All clothing must be decent and appropriate for a public, mixed-audience environment. Excessively revealing,
            fetish-related, or offensive clothing or accessories are not allowed.
          </li>
          <li>Nudity or clothing simulating nudity is not permitted.</li>
          <li>Fursuits and partial suits are welcome but must allow for safe movement and propervisibility.</li>
          <li>
            Fursuiters must ensure their costume is safe to wear in public spaces, does not pose hazards to themselves
            or others, and can be removed quickly in case of emergency.
          </li>
          <li>
            Wearing fursuit parts (tails, ears, paws, etc.) is allowed, but they must not be used inappropriately or
            disruptively.
          </li>
          <li>
            Props or costume parts resembling weapons must be clearly non-functional and may be subject to staff
            inspection.
          </li>
          <li>
            Always treat fursuiters and those wearing costume parts with respect. Do not touch, hug, or interact
            physically with a fursuiter without clear and explicit consent.
          </li>
          <li>
            Do not pull on tails, ears, or other costume parts, even in jest. These actions can damage costumes and may
            be considered harassment.
          </li>
          <li>
            Be mindful of the reduced vision and hearing that fursuiters may experience, and take extra care when
            approaching or speaking to them.
          </li>
          <li>
            Be aware that some items of clothing, apparel, or similar items might bring theconvention and/or fandom into
            disrepute and should not be worn in public. If you have toask or think twice about doing something in
            public, it is a good indication that you shouldtake it to your room.
          </li>
          <li>
            Convention staff reserves the right to determine whether any clothing and/or accessoriescontravene the
            following rules. Questions regarding rules for clothing and outfits should be directed to the department
            head of Stewards &amp; Safety, who can be contacted at <a href="mailto:conops@fluufff.org"
              >conops@fluufff.org</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>4. Photography and media</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Flüüfff may be documented by our official media team. By attending, you give us permission to use
            photographs or video footage of you for promotional purposes. If you do not wish to appear in official
            photos or videos, please notify staff.
          </li>
          <li>
            Personal photography is welcome, but always ask permission before photographing other attendees, especially
            those in fursuit.
          </li>
          <li>Photography is not allowed in designated private areas such as the Dealer's Den.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>5. Health and Safety</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            If you're feeling unwell, refrain from attending convention activities to ensure the health and safety of
            others.
          </li>
          <li>Follow any public health guidance in place.</li>
          <li>Maintain personal hygiene. Follow the "6-2-1" rule: 6 hours of sleep, 2 meals, and 1 shower per day.</li>
          <li>Familiarize yourself with emergency exits and procedures.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>6. Prohibited Items and Activities</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Weapons (real or replica) are not allowed unless explicitly approved by the staff.</li>
          <li>Maintain respectful behavior towards all attendees, staff, and venue personnel.</li>
          <li>Disruptive or aggressive behavior is not acceptable.</li>
          <li>Alcohol is permitted only in designated areas and must comply with local laws.</li>
          <li>Illegal substances are strictly prohibited.</li>
          <li>Be mindful of noise, especially during late hours.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>7. Consequences and Enforcement</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Failure to comply with these rules may result in consequences ranging from warnings to expulsion without
            refund.
          </li>
          <li>In serious cases, the organizers may involve security or local authorities.</li>
          <li>Appeals may be submitted to the organizing committee. Their decision is final.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>8. Questions and Incident Reporting</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            If you have questions about this Code of Conduct or need to report an incident, please contact us through
            the <a href="/contact">Contact</a> page or speak directly with a staff member.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </main>
  </Sidebar>
  <Socials />
</Base>

<style scoped lang="scss">
  @use '../styles/text-styles';
  @use '../styles/charter';

  main {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content {
    padding: 20px 60px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 100%;
    color: charter.$primary800;

    &:first-child {
      padding: 80px 60px 20px 60px;
    }

    &:last-child {
      padding: 20px 60px 80px 60px;
    }

    h1 {
      @include text-styles.heading1;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      @include text-styles.heading4;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    p:not(:last-child) {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    a {
      color: charter.$primary500;
    }

    ul > li {
      list-style-type: disc;
    }
  }
</style>
